<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:302px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Reserves_of_foreign_exchange_and_gold.PNG" class="image" title="Reserves of foreign exchange and gold"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/11/Reserves_of_foreign_exchange_and_gold.PNG/300px-Reserves_of_foreign_exchange_and_gold.PNG" width="300" height="137" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Reserves_of_foreign_exchange_and_gold.PNG" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
Reserves of foreign exchange and gold</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>Of all the <a href="/wiki/Precious_metal" title="Precious metal">precious metals</a>, <a href="/wiki/Gold" title="Gold">gold</a> is the most popular as an investment. Investors generally buy gold as a hedge or safe haven against any economic, political, social, or currency-based crises. These crises include investment market declines, inflation, war, and social unrest. Investors also buy gold during times of a <a href="/wiki/Bull_market#Bull_market" title="Bull market" class="mw-redirect">bull market</a> to gain financially.</p>
